Allow subfolder url rewrite (#896)By setting `custom_base_url` in system.yaml, we can have Grav in a subfolder but run it in the domain root.rnrn## Scenario 1rnrnGrav is installed in `http://localhost:8080/grav-develop` but you want it to respond on `http://localhost:8080`rnrnIn system.yaml, setrnrn```rncustom_base_url: 'http://localhost:8080'rn```rnrnand set the session path to the new Grav site path, rnrn```rnsession:rn  path: /rn```rnrnAnd in the domain root, set the redirect, e.g. with .htaccess:rnrn```rnRewriteEngine OnrnRewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} !^/grav-develop/rnRewriteRule ^(.*)$ /grav-develop/$1rn```rnrnwhere `grav-develop` is the subfolder where Grav is.rnrn## Scenario 2rnrnGrav is installed in `http://localhost:8080/grav-develop` but you want it to respond on `http://localhost:8080/xxxxx`rnrnIn system.yaml, setrnrn```rncustom_base_url: 'http://localhost:8080/xxxxx'rn```rnrnand set the session path to the new Grav site path, rnrn```rnsession:rn  path: /xxxxxrn```rnrnAnd in the new root folder, /xxxxx, set the redirect, e.g. with .htaccess:rnrn```rnRewriteEngine OnrnRewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} !^/grav-develop/rnRewriteRule ^(.*)$ /grav-develop/$1rn```rnrnwhere `grav-develop` is the sister subfolder where Grav is.rn

ImageMedium#derivatives now works with image filters (#1107)* ImageMedium->derivatives now works with image filtersrnrnPreviously, using ImageMedium->derivatives would not work well inrncombination with image filters or the other method of generatingrnsrcset variants of images (by appending eg. @2x to theirrnfilenames). This commit hopefully fixes that.rnrn* Modified initialization of image alternativesrnrnThe biggest alternative will now become the base medium, andrnalternatives will be filled out as necessary in a descendingrnmanner.rnrn* Fully reset image when derivatives method is calledrnrnOtherwise we get some funky results, with the possibility of tworndifferent images being rendered between the full-width srcsetrnversion and the original src version.rnrn* Account for risk of original file not existing when generating image derivativesrnrn* Fixed an issue where too many alternatives would be generatedrnrnWhen using naming conventions to generate image alternatives, thisrnpatch would previously generate a u00e2u0080u009c@1xu00e2u0080u009d alternative if one didnu00e2u0080u0099trnexist. Thatu00e2u0080u0099s no longer the casernrn* Add an @1x alternative when an image lacks a base mediumrnrnWhen an image only has an alternative medium - ie. the onlyrnversion of the image ends in eg. @3x, then we construct thernmissing alternatives automatically. Previously, we would only dornthis down till @2x, meaning that the image that would have beenrnthe base medium, had the image been manually resized, wasn'trncreated. This has now been fixed.rnrn* Always make smallest image alternative the base mediumrnrnWhen an image lacks a base medium on disk (eg. the only existingrnimage is an @2x version), then we make a scaled down version thernbase medium, which ensures that the smaller version is served uprnin the src attribute in the HTML.rnrnAlso, don't reset the image alternatives when callingrnImageMedium#derivatives, instead only generate the imagernalternatives that are missing.rnrn* Set better prettynames for image derivativesrnrn* Changed image derivatives prettynames to be width basedrnrnInstead of example2x.jpeg, we now have eg. example1280w.jpegrn

Fixing a minor bug in Number validation. (#1329)The function validateNumber only checks for numeric values.rnrn**By PHP isNumeric**rnrn42,rn1337,rn0x539,rn02471,rn0b10100111001,rn1337e0,rnnot numeric,rnarray(),rn9.1rnrn**Will evaluate respectively**rnrn'42' is numericrn'1337' is numericrn'1337' is numericrn'1337' is numericrn'1337' is numericrn'1337' is numericrn'not numeric' is NOT numericrn'Array' is NOT numericrn'9.1' is numericrnrnGrav though does not support all value types for a variety of reasons. One being YAML Blueprint definitions, where it makes sense to make a new type value for a more specialized format. Specifically for numbers if a more advance number format it would make sense to make a new type for that number format.rnrnYAML spec specifically allows both Integer or Float contexts, as seen in the validate class validateInt and validateFloat. This is useful when the output formats explicitly needs to be a certain format.rnrnHowever, in the case of generic numeric contexts, which numbers could be floats or ints dynamically, the values are cast back to an int currently in Grav numeric validation. Having dynamic primitive number formats is important, true in an interpreted language like JavaScript where 1 and 1.0 will both work for a number value.rnrnThe reason to cast the type of the variable still is to prevent wide selection of number formats, and to keep Grav in line with primitive YAML field formats.

This was even true when the filterNumber function was giving back a correct parameter. filter_var from validateFloat was actually perserving the float variable type which the YAML engine perserved upon Yaml::dump.rnrnThis is a unconventional fix, but it is the simplest way to handle this edge case.

Add muted and playsinline attributes (#2124)Fixes: #2099rnrnTo be able to add videos to sites that behave as GIFs, two attributes are needed for the videos to be properly handled on iOS and in Chrome: muted and playsinline.rnrnMutedrnChrome only allows videos to autoplay when the contain the muted attribute. Non-muted videos will not autoplay unless the user has interacted with the site. More details here:  https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2017/09/autoplay-policy-changes#new-behaviorsrnrnPlaysinlinernThe playsinline attribute allows developers to specify videos on iPhone should play inline and not automatically enter fullscreen mode when playback begins. More details here: https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2017/09/autoplay-policy-changes#new-behaviors

Fix broken nounce handling (#2121)* Remove deprecated getNonceOldStyle functionrnrnThis commit removes the following functions:rnrn- getNonceOldStylern- generateNonceStringOldStylernrnThe functions have been replaced in newer versions ofrngrav. It seems to me that they only existed in order to make arnupgrade to a newer version of grav painless (i.e. accept both types ofrnnonce tokens). Nowadays, existing old style nonces are expired longrntime ago so it should be save to delete the deprecated funtions.rnrn* Fix caching of nonces in static class variablernrnCurrently, the behavior of `getNonce` is broken because it saves therngenerated nonce in an array and only use the $action as thernkey. However, the generated nonce does not only depend on the $action,rnbut also on $plusOneTick.rnrn* Fix broken plusOneTick for noncesrnrnIt looks to me that there is a bug in the current implemention ofrnverifyNonce. Here is an example:rnrn- 2018-08-01 10:00: We respond to a request and generate a nonce. Thern  current tick is at 35489rnrn- 2018-08-01 10:05: We use the previously generated nonce to makern  another request. We compare the given nounce with a new generatedrn  one (based on the same tick). The result is exactly the same and thern  request succeeds.rnrn- 2018-08-01 14:00: We're now one tick ahead. Remember: A day (24rn  hours) is separated into two ticks (each 12 hours). A request comesrn  in, we compare the given nounce with a newly generated one based onrn  the current tick (now at 35490). They don't match (which is totallyrn  okay).rnrn  If the comparison fails, we then compare the given nounce with arn  another, newly generated one. This time, we pass plusOneTick, torn  the function, which increases the current tick by one. Our tick isrn  now at 35491. We generate a nonce based on that tick and of course,rn  it still does not match the given nonce.rnrn  Instead of increasing the tick, we should rather decreasing it byrn  one (i.e. use the previous tick). If the first comparison fails, wern  use the current tick (35490), decrease it by one (35489) and thenrn  compare it again. 35489 is the same tick as in the very firstrn  request.rnrnThis bug leads to a maximum life time of 12 hours for a nonce and inrnworst case only a few seconds (!)rnrnI would like to prove the bug with an unit test but I'm too unexperiencedrnin PHP. Furthermore it seems that we need some kind of library whichrnis able to mock builtin functions (like time). Maybern<https://github.com/Codeception/AspectMock> would be a good canditate?rn

Fix issue with vUndefined in GPM
Grav 1.6 code cleanup (#2366)* Code cleanuprn* Define admin menu for Flex Usersrn
Use array to make ordering easier
Some bug fixes for Psr-7 & request handler
Allow onRequestHandlerInit to set Response object
Fixed validation for select field type with selectize
Change default attribute value of Flex[class]::getType($prefix) to false
fix dead link + add http > https changes to site urls (#2369)
Fixes issue with uninitialized users object
Fixed `FlexIndex` keys being lost when `FlexCollection` gets loaded
Initialize users before plugins on `bin/plugin` commands
Fixed missing `form_nonce` for JS when using `FlexForm`
Updated `UserInterface` and `FlexObjectInterface` by adding missing update() parameter
Console commands: add method for invalidating cache
display fullname instead of title in list
Fixed `FlexIndex` keys being lost when `FlexCollection` gets loaded
Added getCache() method to FlexIndex, FlexCollection and FlexObject
Renamed flex users blueprints to match the class name, move index file [#2378]
Fixed bug in Flex collection caching
Fix for email causing infinite u00e2u0080u0098callu00e2u0080u0099 recursion
Added support for a backlink in scheduler
Added method to return FlexIndex from FlexCollection
Fixed FlexUser loosing ACL information (apply only for user)
Fixed `FlexUser::find()` breaking when nothing is found
Fixed `FlexObject::update()` removing fields which aren't allowed by ACL
Update changelog by marking fixes/changes between Grav 1.6 beta releases
Disable deprecation messages for Page methods for now (used in too many places)
Improved `File::save()` not to use file lock, but a temporary file, fixed `Obtaining write lock failed on file...`
Improved `File::save()` to use a temporary file if file isn't locked
Added `Flex::getObjects()` and `Flex::getMixedCollection()` methods for co-mingled collections Added support to use single Flex key parameter in `Flex::getObject()` method
Fixed potential undefined property in `onPageNotFound` event handling
FlexObject: When creating object and key isn't set, use storage key instead
Move last backup logging into the backup command
Create set of interfaces for all page methods
Update all classes to rely on `PageInterface` instead of `Page` class
Better error checking in `bin/plugin` for existence and enabled
Regression: index not working due to missing method
Request object: Include attribute for request time
FlexForm: Fix unique id for new objects

Some phpstan issues (#2393)* Fix bug, method init must be protectedrn* Added phpstan level 0rn* Added exclusionsrn* Fix: incorrect case in Twig_SimpleFunctionrn* Fix, no abstract properties, if properties used in methods let's set themrn* Fixed PsrSimpleCacheInvalidArgumentException referenced with incorrect casern* added exclusionsrn* Fixed: Access to an undefined property GravFrameworkFormFormFlash::$uploadObjects.rn* Fixed: does not call parent constructor from GravCommonIterator.rn* Fixed: does not call parent constructor from GravCommonIterator.rn* Fixed: does not call parent constructorrn* Fixed: does not call parent constructorrn* Minor: correct type for inflectorrn* Moved phpstan.neon out of public directoryrn* Added exclusionrn* set GRAV_USER_INSTANCE to prevent LogiException in Userrn* Exlude Stream:creatern* Minor: Missing storage propertyrn* Minor: Fixed missing properties (phpstan level 1)rn* Added type for $datarn* Minor: Ensure $langs is initializedrn* Fix possible bug in $http_response_header status code retrieval (PHP 7.1 only)rn* Added exclusion for $http_response_header (isset is actually not required)rn* Strict null checkrn
Minor fix for FlexUser, changelog update
Fixed some bugs found by phpstan
Fixed phpstan level 2 issues in GravFramework
Preliminary tests for CsvFormatter::encode + minor fix for empty data (#2405)
Fixed some more phpstan level 2 issues
Fixed some phpstan level 2 issues in GravConsole
Reverted commit 48816d9 causing issues with GPM cli commands (ref, getgrav/grav-plugin-admin@e3fc4ce)
Fixed most phpstan level 2 issues in GravCommon
Fixed/silenced the remaining phpstan level 2 issues
Twig nicenumber: do not use 0 + string casting hack
Fixed phpstan level 3 errors in GravFramework
Fixed phpstan level 4 and 5 errors in GravFramework
Better solution for SEO imagename format
site crashes if header is invalid #2343
Added `composer test-plugins` to test plugin issues with the current version of Grav
Class `GravCommonPageMediumAbstractMedia` now use array traits instead of extending `GravCommonGetters`
Greatly improved Flex interfaces and docblocks
Added detection for deprecated features into phpstan
Fixed file saving when temporary file cannot be created to the current folder / stream
Fixed `File::save()` silently ignoring failures with read only streams
Use toolbox 1.4.2 in develop branch for now
Added `Content-Type: application/json` body support for PSR-7 `ServerRequest`

When using Grav behind an HTTPS-endpoint, we would probably have either one of (#2486)* `HTTPS=on`rn* `X-Forwarded-Proto https`rnStill, the latest virtualhost would still provide `REQUEST_SCHEME` which,rncontrary to HTTPS environment, would not be overriden (eg: Apache onlyrncreates `REDIRECT_REQUEST_SCHEME` with the requested value).rnrnThis change gives priority to non-empty `HTTPS` over `REQUEST_SCHEME`.

Update robots.txt (#2632)I have found that Bing/Yahoo/DuckDuckGo, Yandex and Google report crawl errors when using the default robots.txt. Specifically their bots will not crawl the the path '/' or any sub-paths. I agree that the current robots.txt should work and properly implements the specification. However it still does not work.rnrnIn my experience explicitly permitting the path '/' by adding the directive Allow: / resolves the issue.rnrnMore details can be found in a blog post about the issue here: https://www.dfoley.ie/blog/starting-with-the-indieweb

do NOT ignore . dirs OR ignore . dirs and all children (#2581)If you ignore any files beginning with . including directories, then the all() method will exclude .somedir, but not .somedir/somefile. Subsequently, when trying to copy all files returned from all(), it will fail when the method tries to copy a file into a directory that has not yet been created because .somedir was omitted from the return array of all().rnI found this bug when trying to install the admin plugin and ./tmp was a mount and thus rename() failed and self:copy() was invoked instead (line 365).
